headline: From Monroe to Trump: Two centuries of US interference in Latin America
description: From the Monroe Doctrine of 1823 to the intervention in Venezuela, Washington has dominated the American continent by force and through economic power. Faced with China's growing influence, Donald Trump has rejuvenated the notion of a 'manifest destiny.'

headline: 'Trump, hands off Greenland!': From Nuuk to Copenhagen, thousands rally against US annexation plan
By appearing with a royal heiress, Jordan Bardella risks blurring his image
Trump threatens Europe with tariffs over Greenland as protesters rally
description: Denmark, Norway, Sweden, France, Germany, the UK, the Netherlands and Finland would be subject to a 10% tariff on all goods sent to the US, Donald Trump said in a Truth Social post on Saturday, as thousands demonstrated in the capital of Greenland against his plans.

headline: EU and Mercosur sign 'historic' free trade deal
description: Saturday's signing ceremony in Paraguay's capital of Asunción marks a major geopolitical victory for the EU in an age of American tariffs and surging Chinese exports. 'The geopolitical importance of this agreement cannot be overstated,' said Commission President Ursula von der Leyen.

headline: French Response, the foreign ministry's X account for trolling disinformation
description: Since 2025, the unconventional X account French Response has delivered sharp English-language retorts and headline-grabbing moments on the social network. Experts call it an effective way to counter attempts at foreign interference, though it raises questions about its long-term usefulness.

headline: Henrique Gouveia e Melo, the admiral who wants to lead Portugal
description: Revealed during the Covid-19 pandemic, former military officer Henrique Gouveia e Melo is in the race for the January 18 presidential election. He has attracted voters with his talk of reform, despite his limited grasp of political conventions.

How a uranium supply coveted by Russia ended up in limbo in Niger
description: A convoy of trucks loaded with 1,000 metric tons of uranium concentrate left the Arlit mine in Niger on November 27. The shipment was supposed to reach the port of Lomé, Togo, for transfer to a Russian bulk carrier, according to French government sources. Instead, it got stuck at Niamey airport.

headline: Yann Le Cun: 'Why I'm leaving Meta to launch my own AI start-up'
description: The former head of artificial intelligence research at Meta explains his decision to start a new company focused on the physical world, citing strategic differences with the American tech giant and predicting a 'third AI revolution' in the coming years.

headline: Mercosur trade deal will have uneven effects on EU countries
description: From Dutch ultra-productivism to Greek micro-farms, European agriculture – already weakened by climate change, animal epidemics and competition – has struggled to present a united front in response to the free trade agreement.
